body_html:
I didn't make nothing either, I just thought.

I saw the error tracing back to protobuf and I thought two things:

  1. I had compiled right after the release of tf 1.7 successfully (right after march 30) and now I was compiling the tf 1.8 and nothing appear to be right.

  2. I could not blame the entire repository of tf for this they would not let everybody down like this. Then may be that package or another one could be the problem.

Then I tought... "protobuf" what was the time of my previous tensorflow build that actually get success and investigated at pypi.org. Next I asked myself what was the protobuf that I could have on my machine on that time I get everything successfull?

I just find out that the release date of the package was days after my last build on Tf 1.7. Then I relealised that could be it.

body:
I didn't make nothing either, I just thought.

I saw the error tracing back to protobuf and I thought two things:
1. I had compiled right after the release of tf 1.7 successfully  (right after march 30) and now I was compiling the  tf 1.8 and nothing appear to be right. 

2. I could not blame the entire repository of tf for this they would not let everybody down like this. Then may be that package or another one could be the problem.

Then I tought... "protobuf" what was the time of my previous tensorflow build that actually get success and investigated at [pypi.org](https://pypi.org/project/protobuf/#history). Next I asked myself what was the protobuf that I could have on my machine on that time I get everything successfull?

I just find out that the release date of the package was days after my last build on Tf 1.7. Then I relealised that could be it.
